    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Systematics and natural history of Southeast Asian Rock Geckos (genus Cnemaspis Strauch, 1887) with descriptions of eight new species from Malaysia, Thailand, and Indonesia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949582>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949584>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949572>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949568> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949582>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Adult male Cnemaspis monachorum (LSUDPC 6502) from Pulau Langgun of the Langkawi Archipelago, Kedah, Peninsular Malaysia in the dark color pattern phase. Photograph by LLG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4949582/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949584>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Cnemaspis monachorum (LSUDPC 6502) from the Langkawi Archipelago, Kedah, Peninsular Malaysia. Upper and middle left: ventral color pattern of male (upper; LSUDPC 8275) and female (middle; LSUDPC 8274) from Pulau Langgun. Photographs by ESHQ. Upper right: adult male (LSUDPC 4701) from Wat Wanaram, Pulau Langkawi in the dark color pattern phase. Lower left: adult female (LSUDPC 4846) from Wat Wanaram in the dark color pattern phase. Lower right: karst microhabitat on Pulau Langgun. Photographs by LLG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4949584/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949572>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distribution of the species in the Pattani and Southern Sunda clades. Stars indicate type localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4949572/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4949568>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Maximum-likelihood phylogram (–InL 73957.608688) of the species of the genus Cnemaspis with Bayesian posterior probabilities (BPP) and maximum-likelihood (ML) bootstrap values, respectively based on the concatenated 3 gene dataset. Black circles are nodes supported by BBP and ML values greater than 0.95 and 70, respectively. Gray circles are nodes supported only by ML values greater than 70. White circles are nodes supported only by BPP values greater than 0.95. The distribution maps on the right delimit the ranges of the four major clades." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4949568/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

